# backend-template — Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: NestJS (Express) + TypeScript 5.4
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 16 via Prisma ORM
- **Cache**: Redis 7 via ioredis
- **Auth**: JWT (passport) + OAuth2 social login
- **Encryption**: AES-256-GCM
- **Logging**: Winston + Loki
- **Tracing**: OpenTelemetry + Jaeger

## Architecture
- Hybrid monolith (`main/`) + microservices (`microservices/`)
- Global guards: JwtAuthGuard + RolesGuard
- Validation: class-validator DTOs + global ValidationPipe (whitelist, forbidNonWhitelisted)
- All DB access via Prisma (no raw SQL)

## Security Constraints
- Every authenticated endpoint must use @UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)
- Admin endpoints must add @Roles('ADMIN') + RolesGuard
- Refresh tokens are rotated (SHA-256 hash in refresh_tokens table)
- Token theft detection: reused revoked tokens trigger full session revocation
- User.isActive verified on every JWT request

